{"id":"313884299_Multiple_Attribute_Decision_Making_Based_on_Interval-Valued_Intuitionistic_Fuzzy_Sets_Linear_Programming_Methodology_and_the_Extended_TOPSIS_Method","abstract":"In recent years, some multiple attribute decision making (MADM) methods have been presented based on interval-valued intuitionistic fuzzy sets (IVIFSs). In this paper, we propose a new MADM method based on IVIFSs, the linear programming (LP) methodology, and the extension of the technique for order preference by similarity to ideal solution (TOPSIS) method, where the LP methodology is used to obtain optimal weights of attributes. The proposed method can overcome the drawbacks of the existing methods for MADM in interval-valued intuitionistic fuzzy (IVIF) environments.","authors":["Cheng-Yi Wang","Shyi-Ming Chen"],"meta":["February 2017Information Sciences 397","DOI:10.1016/j.ins.2017.02.045"],"references":["308709624_Shadowed_sets_of_dynamic_fuzzy_sets","306310941_Inclusion_degree_with_variable-precision_model_in_analyzing_inconsistent_decision_tables","305952852_Membership_grade_mining_of_mutually_inverse_fuzzy_implication_propositions","304924033_Robust_decision_making_using_intuitionistic_fuzzy_numbers","304405089_An_overview_of_interval-valued_intuitionistic_fuzzy_information_aggregations_and_applications","301794030_Rule_Based_Systems_A_Granular_Computing_Perspective","295688156_Granular_computing_as_a_basis_of_human-data_interaction_A_cognitive_cities_use_case","294283438_A_comparison_of_three_approaches_for_estimating_synthesizing_an_interval_type-2_fuzzy_set_model_of_a_linguistic_term_for_computing_with_words","289501761_Bridging_gaps_between_several_forms_of_granular_computing","287419543_Managing_multi-granularity_linguistic_information_in_qualitative_group_decision_making_An_overview","281593947_lijisuansanyuanlun_Triarchic_Theory_of_Granular_Computing","224105509_TOPSIS-Based_Nonlinear-Programming_Methodology_for_Multiattribute_Decision_Making_With_Interval-Valued_Intuitionistic_